// ── The catalog, assembled ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// WHY THIS BLOCK EXISTS AT ALL, stated plainly: for a while this file held every record above and
// exported NOTHING. The arrays were module-private, so `spellCatalog('dnd5e-2014')` fell through to
// its EMPTY case and every 2014 spell picker in the app showed an empty list — while the repo's
// orphan-module guard carried an exemption predicting exactly that ("if this entry is still here
// and the file has exports, the dispatcher wiring was forgotten").
//
// AUTHORED AND REACHABLE ARE DIFFERENT THINGS. 200 verified spell records that nothing can import
// are worth precisely as much as no spell records at all, and they are worse in one respect: they
// look done. The export block and the dispatcher registration are not paperwork on top of the real
// work — they ARE the point at which the work starts existing.

/** Every catalogued 2014 spell, in level order. */
